# Side panel z-index (always behind header)

When adjusting **any** side panel (Character Studio right rail, left tool sidebar, collapsed icon strip, or future panels):

## Invariant

**Side panels must always render behind `.app-header` in z-index.** They must never overlap or cover the header band.

## Stacking order (low → high)

| Layer | Token / class | z-index |
|-------|----------------|---------|
| Side panels | `--z-side-panel` / `.opennexus-sidebar`, `.sidebar` overlays | **998** |
| App header | `--z-app-header` / `.app-header` | **1001** |
| Scene controls row | `--z-scene-controls` / `.scene-controls-row` | **1002** |

- Side panel `z-index` must stay **strictly below 1001** (use `var(--z-side-panel)`).
- Do **not** raise side panels to 1003+ to fix overlap — fix `top` / layout instead (see `memory-bank/app-chrome-layout-protected-state.md`).
- `.opennexus-sidebar` is `position: fixed` with `top: var(--app-content-top)` (measured); if icons sit under scene-controls, lower `top` — do not raise z-index.

## Checklist when changing side panel layout

1. Confirm side panel z-index ≤ `--z-side-panel` (998).
2. Confirm `.app-header` remains at `--z-app-header` (1001) or higher.
3. Never set side panel or its children above the header unless the element is intentionally part of the header chrome (e.g. tooltips with their own stacking).
